The natural assumption to make about the ordered phase outside the SK model (which corresponds to the limit of infinite dimensionality) is that it is similar to that of the SK model in having many pure states. However, we have argued elsewhere (Moore and Bray 1985) that for d < 6 there is only a single pure state (or rather two pure states, counting the time-reversed state). This implies a trivial P ( q ) :

