Equation (35) shows that at least to first order in E, P ( q ) is trivial and that the spin glass is apparently replica symmetric, i.e. it consists of basically a single pure state. It is difficult to see how higher-order terms in the E expansion could ever modify this
result. We suspect, therefore that for f < (T < 1 replica symmetry is obtained. For v <$
no RG treatment is possible; one proceeds via a loop expansion about the mean-field theory. When this is a valid procedure we expect replica symmetry breaking to occur. Bhatt and Young (1985) have performed Monte Carlo simulations for the onedimensional long-range model, but to date they have not calculated P ( q ) outside the
mean-field limit. A Monte Carlo simulation of P(q ) would be a highly desirable check
on these calculations.

